  "text": "T (BA) is close to a diagonal matrix (in a sense made precise in Theorem 5). Let X be a real-valued symmetric random variable such that E(|X| 1+γ ) ≤ M for some M > 1 and 0 < γ < 1. The following lemma from [CITATION_1] says that the empirical average of the absolute value of X converges to the expectation of |X|. The proof, which we omit, follows an argument similar to the proof of the Chebyshev's inequality. LetẼ N [|X|] be the empirical average obtained from N independent samples X (1) , . . . , X (N ) , i.e., (",
